text.tspan: Attendance vs enrollment rates, primary education, 2015
The horizontal axis shows the net enrollment rate (total number of students in the age group for primary education enrolled in that level,
expressed as a percentage of the total population in that age group). The vertical axis shows net attendance rate proportion of children of the
official primary school age who are attending primary school (household survey data).
Net enrollment rate. Primary. Both sexes (%)
Net attendance rate. Primary. Both sexes (%)
Data source: Demographic and Health Surveys (DHS), UNESCO Institute for Statistics
